 JOHANNESBURG - President Jacob Zuma joined in a song praising Nkosazana Dlamini-Zuma on Wednesday, adding his voice to his ex-wife's bid to succeed him.Women's Day celebrations in the Northern Cape were turned into a campaign rally for Dlamini-Zuma.Hundreds of attendees in Galeshewe, Kimberly sang loudly, We are ready for Nkosazana , endorsing her campaign ahead of the ANC's elective conference in December. READ: President publicly endorses Dlamini-Zuma as successor eNCA